{"kind":"project","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/ManagerCreation"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[{"title":"Creating and managing TWSManager","chapter":"Display your first snippet","kind":"hero","estimatedTimeInMinutes":5,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Learn different ways of creating and managing TWSManager","type":"text"}]}]},{"tasks":[{"anchor":"Manager-creation-and-registration","title":"Manager creation and registration","stepsSection":[{"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First way to create a TWSManager is by using TWSFactory.new(with:)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You provide the factory with your project id and the factory creates or retrieves(if instance for the configuration is already alive) a TWSManager instance for the provided configuration."}]}],"caption":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the instance was created for the first time, you have to register it with remote services to use it. Call registerManager() on the manager instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"}],"media":null,"code":"ManagerCreation_00.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Another way to create a manager is by using View extension function twsRegister(configuration:), which creates a TWSManager instance with the provided configuration, injects it into the view hiearchy and registers it with remote services.","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use @Environment(TWSManager.self) to retrieve manager in ancestor views."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This way the manager will persist automatically as long as that view hierarchy is alive."}]}]}],"media":null,"code":"ManagerCreation_01.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Last way to do it is using combination of both. You can create an instance using TWSFactory.new(with:) and then register and inject it into the environment using View extension function twsRegister(using:)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"caption":[],"media":null,"code":"ManagerCreation_02.swift","runtimePreview":null}],"contentSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this section you will learn different approaches for creation, registration with remote services and persistance of the TWSManager.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing"}]}],"kind":"tasks"},{"title":"Combine remote and local snippets","action":{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/MixAndMatch","overridingTitle":"Get started","type":"reference","isActive":true},"kind":"callToAction","abstract":[{"text":"Once you start mixing remote and local snippets, there are a few important considerations to keep in mind. Since the manager is injected into the environment, it can be accessed from anywhere in the app. However, this setup assumes that snippets are handled remotely. To successfully work with both remote and local snippets, you’ll need to follow specific rules and best practices.","type":"text"}],"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial"}],"metadata":{"category":"Learn to use the SDK","role":"project","categoryPathComponent":"Tutorial-Table-of-Contents","title":"Creating and managing TWSManager"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents","doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents\/$volume","doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents\/Display-your-first-snippet"]],"modules":[{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/LocalSnippet","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/LocalSnippet#Displaying-a-Snippet","kind":"task"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet#Connect-with-the-TWS-portal","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet#Presenting-snippets","kind":"task"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/ManagerCreation","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/ManagerCreation#Manager-creation-and-registration","kind":"task"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/MixAndMatch","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/MixAndMatch#Mix-Match","kind":"task"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/Notifications","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/Notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents\/Display-your-first-snippet"},{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomizingViews","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomizingViews#Custom-loading-and-error-views"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomInterceptor","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomInterceptor#Custom-interceptors"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents\/Customizing-TWSView"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/tws\/managercreation"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents":{"title":"Getting Started","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/Tutorial-Table-of-Contents","url":"\/tutorials\/tutorial-table-of-contents","abstract":[{"text":"Follow the tutorials to learn how to use the SDK for displaying snippets.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"overview","kind":"overview"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/ManagerCreation":{"url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/managercreation","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/ManagerCreation","title":"Creating and managing TWSManager","role":"project","kind":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn different ways of creating and managing TWSManager"}],"estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/ManagerCreation#Manager-creation-and-registration":{"title":"Manager creation and registration","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/ManagerCreation#Manager-creation-and-registration","kind":"section","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn different ways of creating and managing TWSManager"}],"role":"pseudoSymbol","type":"section","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/managercreation#Manager-creation-and-registration"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/CustomInterceptor":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to intercept desired URLs and use them in native flows"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/custominterceptor","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomInterceptor","type":"topic","role":"project","title":"Intercepting URL requests","estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/Notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications":{"title":"Integrating TWSNotifications","role":"pseudoSymbol","kind":"section","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In this tutorial you will learn how to easily integrate TWSNotifications in your existing push notification code base."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/Notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/notifications#Integrating-TWSNotifications","type":"section"},"ManagerCreation_02.swift":{"syntax":"swift","highlights":[{"line":5},{"line":8}],"identifier":"ManagerCreation_02.swift","fileType":"swift","fileName":"ContentView.swift","content":["import SwiftUI","import TWS","","struct ContentView: View {","    @State var manager = TWSFactory.new(with: TWSBasicConfiguration(id: \"projectId\"))","    var body: some View {","        HomeView()","            .twsRegister(using: manager)","    }","}","","struct HomeView: View {","    @Environment(TWSManager.self) var manager","    var body: some View {","        ZStack {","            if let snippet = manager.snippets().first(where: { $0.id == \"snippetId\" }) {","                TWSView(snippet: snippet)","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"file"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/RemoteSnippet#Connect-with-the-TWS-portal":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet#Connect-with-the-TWS-portal","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/remotesnippet#Connect-with-the-TWS-portal","kind":"section","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to set up a manager to handle the logic and functionality of your snippets, as well as how to seamlessly integrate them into your SwiftUI views.","type":"text"}],"type":"section","title":"Connect with the TWS portal","role":"pseudoSymbol"},"ManagerCreation_00.swift":{"content":["import SwiftUI","import TWS","","struct ContentView: View {","    \/\/ Create snippet with TWSFactory","    @State var manager = TWSFactory.new(with: TWSBasicConfiguration(id: \"projectId\"))","    ","    var body: some {","        ZStack {","            if let snippet = manager.snippets().first(where: { $0.id == \"snippetId\" }) {","                TWSView(snippet: snippet)","            }","        }.onAppear {","            \/\/ Register manager with remote services","            manager.registerManager()","        }","    }","}"],"identifier":"ManagerCreation_00.swift","type":"file","highlights":[],"fileName":"ContentView.swift","fileType":"swift","syntax":"swift"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/RemoteSnippet":{"type":"topic","role":"project","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/RemoteSnippet","title":"Display your first remote snippet","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to set up a manager to handle the logic and functionality of your snippets, as well as how to seamlessly integrate them into your SwiftUI views.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/remotesnippet","estimatedTime":"3min"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/CustomizingViews#Custom-loading-and-error-views":{"title":"Custom loading and error views","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomizingViews#Custom-loading-and-error-views","type":"section","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/customizingviews#Custom-loading-and-error-views","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to customize your view to fit your applications profile."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Customize loading, preloading and error views.","type":"text"}],"kind":"section","role":"pseudoSymbol"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/CustomizingViews":{"estimatedTime":"3min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to customize your view to fit your applications profile."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Customize loading, preloading and error views."}],"role":"project","kind":"project","title":"Customize views to fit your application","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/customizingviews","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/CustomizingViews"},"doc://tws-ios.TWS/tutorials/TWS/MixAndMatch#Mix-Match":{"title":"Mix & Match","role":"pseudoSymbol","url":"\/tutorials\/tws\/mixandmatch#Mix-Match","identifier":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/MixAndMatch#Mix-Match","kind":"section","type":"section","abstract":[{"text":"Once you start mixing remote and local snippets, there are a few important considerations to keep in mind. Since the manager is injected into the environment, it can be accessed from anywhere in the app. However, this setup assumes that snippets are handled remotely. To successfully work with both remote and local snippets, you’ll need to follow specific rules and best practices.","type":"text"}]},